  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p><p>Place on a baking tray, drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then put them in the oven for 30-40 min until golden</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/404.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/404.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/404.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/404.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/404.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the<strong> tomato ketchup</strong>, <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong>, <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> and <strong>honey</strong> with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong> in a large mixing bowl</p><p>Season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and stir it all together – this is your<strong> BBQ sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/404.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/404.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/404.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/404.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/404.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Place your hand flat onto the <strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Slice in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, so you are left with two thinner pieces</p><p>Add the chicken to the<strong> BBQ sauce</strong> and mix to coat thoroughly – this is your <strong>BBQ chicken</strong></p><p>Refrigerate until step 5</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/404.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
